data.name: DataSourceDownloadMsg
data.value:
Available through December 31, 2009, Blue Book Data Source is an archive that is updated quarterly, containing Blue Book data in ASCII text format. Files are comma delimited surrounded by quotes and contain the following Blue Book information: Blue Book ID Number, Blue Book "Section" (i.e. Produce, Transportation, Supply), Volume and Blue Book Rating, License Information (i.e. PACA, CFIA), Company Name, Address (Mailing and Physical), Phone/FAX/E-Mail/Web Site.

Blue Book Data Source makes it possible for you to view and use Blue Book information on your computer system. For example, Blue Book Data Source can be imported into a custom database program and used for your specific applications. Common applications include relational database programs, contact management software, or your own custom-developed proprietary customer database.

Data Source will only be published through December 31, 2009. If your company uses Data Source, please contact a Blue Book Sales Representative to discuss transitioning to Blue Book Web Services.

By clicking on a file name, the contents of that file will open in a new window. If you wish to download the file, you can right-click on the file and choose "Save Target As" and save the file to a place on your computer. To download all files as a .zip file, click on the "DataSourceFiles.zip" link.

data.name: EBBConversionInstructions
data.value:
Please execute the following steps to convert your EBB Classic Notes and Watchdog Groups into the Blue Book Online Service ({0}). Please note that this is a one-time conversion and that once this data has been converted into the {0}, it cannot be converted again. Therefore, plan on using {0} to manage your Notes and Watchdog lists going forward after this conversion is complete.

Conversion Notes:
  • Only company Notes and Watchdog lists will be converted.
  • All converted data will be marked "Is Private."
  • Special formatting of company Notes will not be converted. Line breaks and spacing will be converted, but the use of colors, fonts, and other special formatting will not be converted.

Steps to Convert EBB Classic Notes and Watchdog Lists:
  1. Start the EBB 5 User Table Utility. From your computer's Start menu, select All Programs, then The Electronic Blue Book Version 5, then EBB 5 User Table Utility.
  2. Select the "Backup Data" tab.
  3. The default location of the backup file will be C:\EBBBKP.ZIP.
  4. Click the "Backup" button.
  5. Once the backup has completed, click the "Exit" button.
  6. Using the "Browse" button below, navigate to the C: drive and select the EBBBKP.ZIP, then click the "Open" button in that dialog window.
  7. Click the "Convert" button to complete the process.
  8. Note: This process may take several minutes. Please only click "Convert" once.
If you need further assistance, please contact our Help Desk at 630 668-3500 or {1}.
